{
  "stem": "6076.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My-- my younger brother, Leibl, he was two years younger than my brother Zisman.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He was a scholar-- a very, very, very highly educated.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He learned in the Lublin Yeshiva, which my parents were very proud of him.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He was good-looking.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He had also blue eyes, blond hair.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He looked more Irish.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I always look forward for the holidays he should come home.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was-- he didn't wear payots at the Lublin Yeshiva.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was wearing more like in a suit-- in a dark suit.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But little payot around under his ears that we couldn't see it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he-- he studied at the end before the war, when he came home, you know.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He studied so much that my father sometimes was afraid that he is bending down, that he's changing on the other side talking about the communism, talking about the Trotsky, about Lenin.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He read about them.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my father, you know, couldn't understand to send him to the Lublin Yeshiva, and coming home he's starting to talk about them.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He says, why do you tell-- and he brought up the whole system and everything.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I heard them.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Sometimes my father quarrelled with him.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He didn't like that idea.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But, of course, he wanted to please my parents.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He-- he stopped.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He didn't talk.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, to please his parents, he will take the Talmud and go to the [INAUDIBLE] and sit and learn for a couple of hours and come home with a smile.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "If he learned there or not, his mind was in a different direction, we don't know about that.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But to please the parents, respect, and koved, that was the most important at home.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Koved means respect.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Next brother was Berl.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
